    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-13T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-13T05:00:00-05:00" n="13"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/857: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kliefoth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-13T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 13, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 13—7:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. The Socialist strike in Vienna developed into general Socialist revolt all
                    over Austria against the Government but which found little public sympathy. The
                    Government forces including army are breaking up the resistance rapidly. The
                    Socialist Party has been dissipated and the Socialist regime of Vienna ousted.
                    The Government estimates 50 killed and several hundred wounded. The Government
                    now seems to have revolt well under control although stubborn resistance in
                    Socialist sections of Vienna continues. The suppressed revolt of the
                    Socialiset[s] means that Dollfuss will no longer enjoy their tolerance in his
                    fight against the Nazis. No reports of Americans injured or molested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kliefoth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
